<HEADLINE>
THEY'RE POLLS APART  
 UCLA, NOT OHIO ST., LEADS 1ST BCS RANKING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By KENT SOMERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Bowl Championship Series ranking made its debut Monday and
wasted little time in generating controversy.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA, ranked second in the Associated Press and coaches polls,
earned the top spot in the BCS ratings. Ohio State, ranked first in
both polls all season, is second. Tennessee, Kansas State and
Florida State round out the top five. Arizona is 14th.
</P>
<P>
   The top two teams in the BCS standings at the end of the year
will play in the Tostitos Fiesta Bowl Jan. 4 in Sun Devil Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``It really doesn't matter to me whether we are ranked first or
second in the BCS poll,'' UCLA Coach Bob Toledo said. ``The
important thing is to have a chance to play in the championship
game, and you can do that being ranked first or second.''
</P>
<P>
   Ohio State Coach John Cooper and the Buckeyes claim they aren't
bothered by the BCS poll.
</P>
<P>
   ``We can't worry about the BCS ratings, just like we can't worry
about our rankings in the national polls,'' Cooper said. ``I can
say that we are happy to be ranked as high as we are in the polls.
We've been the No. 1 team in both the major polls all season, and
we are just going to keep working hard to try and win football
games. Winning takes care of everything.''
</P>
<P>
   The BCS ranking is based on a formula that includes a team's
record, strength of schedule, average ranking in the AP and coaches
polls, and the average rating of three computer polls.
</P>
<P>
   Teams earn points based on the four categories, and the ones
with the lowest totals are ranked highest. The BCS rankings will be
released each Monday and include 20 teams. UCLA leads the standings
with a 3.04 point total _ two points for poll average, one for
computer average, 0.04 for strength of schedule and zero for
losses. Ohio State has 4.31 points _ one for poll average, 2.67 for
computer average, 0.64 for strength of schedule and zero for
losses.
</P>
<P>
   John Junker, the executive director of the Fiesta Bowl, said he
was a little bit surprised that UCLA was No. 1 in the BCS standings
instead of Ohio State. ``I thought it was interesting that in the
three (computer rankings), UCLA was one, one and one,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA was ranked ahead of the Buckeyes by virtue of its strength
of schedule and computer rankings, which rely heavily on strength
of schedule. The computer rankings have the Pac-10 rated higher
than the Big 10.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA has victories over Oregon, ranked 12th in the AP poll, and
Arizona, which is 14th. Ohio State counters with wins over No. 10
Penn State, No. 18 Missouri and No. 21 West Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   The distance between the two teams would have been much closer a
week ago, before Missouri and West Virginia lost, weakening the
Buckeyes computer ranking and strength of schedule numbers.
</P>
<P>
   One recent theory to surface is that the Buckeyes' schedule
could keep them out of national championship game in the Fiesta
Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Ohio State could finish undefeated and rated No. 1 in both polls
yet be ranked behind other schools, such as UCLA, Tennessee or
Florida State, in the BCS standings.
</P>
<P>
   ``But `could' is a much different word than `will', '' Junker
said when asked if a No. 1-ranked Ohio State could be bypassed for
the Fiesta Bowl. ``It's statistically possible but I don't see it
as very likely.''
</P>
<P>
   It's early for fans to get too worked up about the BCS poll,
because there is great potential for it to change.
</P>
<P>
   Its strength of schedule component is based on what opponents a
school has already played. Ohio State, for instance, could receive
a boost by beating No. 22 Michigan on Nov. 21.
</P>
<P>
   And the Buckeyes would also be helped if their opponents were to
win out. The Ohio State faithful will have to swallow hard and hope
Michigan beats No. 9 Wisconsin (8-0) on Nov. 14, because Wisconsin
and Ohio State don't meet this year.
</P>
<P>
   There are several other huge games left to play. Nebraska, sixth
in the BCS ratings, plays Kansas State, rated fourth, on Nov. 14.
And Florida State, which is fifth, plays No. 7 Florida on Nov. 21.
</P>
<P>
   The BCS system was designed to provide an unbiased way to match
the top two teams in one bowl game to determine a national
championship. If there are more than two unbeaten teams, however,
things will get sticky.
</P>
<P>
   ``The problem you're going to have is if you have two teams
playing for the national championship and you've go three or four
teams who feel like they deserve to be in there,'' Cooper told
``The Columbus Dispatch.'' ``You can't please everybody.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
