<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDINALS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SWANN MAY NEED ARTHRO SCOPIC SURGERY ON KNEE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Cardinals fear defensive tackle Eric Swann's arthritic left
knee is so sore he might have to have arthroscopic surgery and miss
a few games.
</P>
<P>
   Swann left the team's Tempe training facility before Monday's
practice to have the knee re-examined by team doctors.
</P>
<P>
   Teammates said the knee had become swollen and didn't improve
during the three days off the players were given over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Cardinals officials are expected to learn the seriousness of the
injury today.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's something that continues to bother him,'' said Cardinals
Coach Vince Tobin, whose team returns to action Sunday at Detroit.
``He's unable to practice on a consistent basis.''
</P>
<P>
   Swann played against Chicago Oct. 11 and the New York Giants
Oct. 18 despite not practicing all week.
</P>
<P>
   ```He has to get himself healthy,'' linebacker Jamir Miller
said. ``If he's out there only halfway, he's not helping us.''
</P>
<P>
   Defensive tackle Mark Smith said it has been obvious for weeks
that Swann has been playing in pain.
</P>
<P>
   ``He thought he could help the team by not practicing and
playing on Sunday,'' Smith said. ``He probably could have gotten
better by doing whatever he needed to get done earlier. The pain
has been lingering on. If he's hurting that bad, he should get the
work (possible surgery) done so he can come back healthy in two or
three weeks.''
</P>
<P>
   Tobin said Swann would be replaced by second-year pro Rashod
Swinger if he can't play against the Lions.
</P>
<P>
   Swann is tied for the team lead in sacks with four and is tied
for second among linemen in tackles with 36.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'd miss Swann,'' Tobin said. ``He's a force not many teams
have, and he has played well when he's been in there. He has the
ability to dominate the middle and force a double-team.'' &QL; 
 &QL; 
Slow healing
</P>
<P>
   Starting cornerback Tom Knight, who has missed the past three
games because of a knee injury, didn't practice again on Monday and
likely won't play against the Lions.
</P>
<P>
   ``It does not look very good for this week,'' Tobin said. ``I
don't know when he's coming back.''
</P>
<P>
   Knight would be replaced again by J.B. Brown, who played well
against Oakland and Chicago but was benched in the second quarter
of the 34-7 loss to the Giants.
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals secondary should be tested Sunday. The Lions'
Herman Moore and Johnnie Morton are one of the league's best wide
receiver tandems.
</P>
<P>
   Knight practiced last Wednesday, but the knee swelled on him
that night, and he has been out since.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was gung-ho last week because I hadn't been able to do
something for so long,'' Knight said. ``Every week, I think this is
the week.'' &QL; 
 &QL; 
Eye sore
</P>
<P>
   Backup cornerback J.J. McCleskey, out the past four games
because of a knee injury, has been running without any problems in
practice.
</P>
<P>
   But he suffered a black eye Monday when rookie safety Corey
Chavous poked him in the eye.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm sorry about it, but I think I improved his looks,''
Chavous joked.
</P>
<P>
   The injury occurred when Chavous got his hand caught in
McCleskey's helmet.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm no longer cute,'' McCleskey said. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Rasslin' update &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   About 20 players rode a bus to America West Arena Monday
afternoon to attend World Championship Wrestling's Monday Nitro
show.
</P>
<P>
   Safety Tommy Bennett said he could see himself being a pro
wrestler someday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'd be known as `Street Smarts,' '' he said. ``I'd come into
the ring with chains and knives. Of course, I wouldn't use them.''
</P>
<P>
   Offensive guard Chris Dishman said his favorite wrestler goes by
the name of ``Goldberg.'' He's Bill Goldberg, former Los Angeles
Rams and Atlanta Falcons defensive tackle.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's only won 152 in a row,'' Dishman said. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Short shots
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals are expected to bring in a couple of defensive
linemen for a tryout today because of the uncertainity of Swann's
injury.
</P>
<P>
   Miller has had the cast taken off his dislocated left wrist and
now wears a splint.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
