   ``OPERA'S DYNAMIC DUO.'' From W magazine. One color slide. Even
for La Scala, home to the world's most factious opera fans, the
booing suffered by soprano Renee Fleming and tenor Marcello
Giordani was remarkable. During the first act of ``Lucrezia
Borgia,'' Fleming sings a showy aria while the tenor lies sleeping.
From her first note, a group of men in the La Scala's nosebleed
seats began to boo her loudly. But Fleming finished her trills and
roused her partner for a duet _ only to discover that the conductor
had fainted. Take about a disaster. Find out how out how two of
opera's shining stars survived this performance _ and how they
intend to scale the heights this fall _ in this profile from W
magazine.
