</P>
<P>
   sounds of the area as launch day approaches. (Bruce, Dayton
Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   BAXTER _ ATLANTA _It's a token of the headline writers' art that
so much of this year's confusing, muddled election picture can be
summed up in a single multi-purpose, one-column line: ``Low Tax
Sought.'' How big money has brought loopiness to the core of
American politics. (Baxter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   INTERBEV _ Continued coverage of InterBev, the beverage
industry's annual convention. (Gramig, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SOUCOM _ ATLANTA _ Southern Co. makes another move into Texas
with agreement to become wholesale electric power supplier to an
electric cooperative that serves the Dallas-Fort Worth area. The
company will also manage the electic power generators of Brazos
Electric Power Cooperative. Last month, Southern announced plans to
purchase s amall power plant in the same area. It's another chaper
in the company's rivalry with Houston-based Enron Corp. (Quinn,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ABORTION-WEB _ (TENTATIVE ) In the wake of abortion provider Dr.
Barnett Slepian's slaying - critics have turned on Neal Horsley,
Carrollton creator of an anti-abortion website that listed Slepian
with a line through his name - as inciting violence by listing the
names and personal information about doctors that perform
abortions. Trying for comment from doctors and Horsley on whether
the Internet provides a new tool for electronic terrorism that
might force some docs out of the business. (Lore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
