</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-1STLD-WRITETHRU-HNS </SLUG>
  
 Tuesday, Oct. 27, 1998     
 Editors     
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service will file these stories for Wednesday.
If you have questions, please call Susie McBee or Tim Spence at
202-298-6920. For questions about Houston Chronicle sports stories,
please call the Houston Chronicle Sports Department, 713-220-7896.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ADDS: GLENN-FEVER; GLENN-MISSION; CLINTON-WOMEN;
FBN-NFL-AGENDAS; and FBC-TRICKS.)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all sluglines.)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GLENN-FEVER (Cape Canaveral, Fla.) _ John Glenn seems as
mystified as anyone about why his return to space is getting so
much attention. Hundreds of thousands of people have converged on
the Cape to watch Thursday's launch, requests for media credentials
are soaring and the residents of Perth, Australia, plan to leave
their lights on for Glenn just like they did for his last space
mission _ in 1962. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
