<HEADLINE>
THAT'S BOND, JAMES BOND, TIMES 20
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Never said ``Never'': S.B. of Haltom City, Texas, called the
trivia line to note that a 20th James Bond film was omitted in a
recent answer: ``Never Say Never Again,'' starring Sean Connery.
</P>
<P>
   MGM, the producer of 18 Bond films and the in-progress ``Bond
19,'' doesn't count ``Never'' because it was filmed independently
of the studio. Producer Kevin McClory has some rights to the Bond
character and ``Thunderball'' script that stem from a legal battle
with Bond creator Ian Fleming. He exercised these rights by
remaking the film as ``Never Say Never Again'' in 1983.
</P>
<P>
   The title played off Connery's longstanding response when asked
if he would ever return to the role: ``Never again.''
</P>
<P>
   In July, MGM obtained a preliminary injunction against Sony
Corp.'s plans to make another Bond film based on rights it acquired
from McClory. McClory and other film executives are giving
depositions this month in the ongoing case.
</P>
<P>
   Q: My son was named after Andy Griffith. How can I write to him?
</P>
<P>
   _ D.D., Burleson, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Griffith in care of the William Morris Agency, 151
El Camino Drive, Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   According to his agency, the 72-year-old actor recently
completed filming ``Daddy and Them,'' a dark comedy with Billy Bob
Thornton as writer, director and performer. Co-stars include Laura
Dern, Ben Affleck and Jim Varney.
</P>
<P>
   The best source for information about Griffith is a fan club
devoted to his best-remembered series: The ``Andy Griffith Show''
Rerun Watchers Club. To join for a year and receive three issues of
its 24-page newsletter, send $12 to TAGSRWC, 9 Music Square S.,
Suite 146, Nashville, TN 37203-3203.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How can I send a letter to Leslie Nielsen?
</P>
<P>
   _ E.C., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to the ``Naked Gun'' and ``Airplane!'' star in care of
Bresler Kelly and Associates, 11500 W. Olympic Blvd., Suite 510,
Los Angeles, CA 90064.
</P>
<P>
   Nielsen, 72, already has three films lined up for 1999 that
involve ships: ``Titanic Too: It Missed the Iceberg,'' ``Love Boat:
The Movie'' and ``2001: A Space Travesty.''
</P>
<P>
   Another project that may be in the works is a ``Naked Gun''
sequel, Nielsen told a St. Louis Post-Dispatch reporter in
December.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
