   EMBASSIES-REFORM _ WASHINGTON _ In an era in which information
moves at the speed of light and unpredictable security threats lurk
around the world, the creaky machinery of U.S. diplomacy is
``barely out of the quill-and-scroll stage'' and needs a major
overhaul to protect American interests, warned a panel of experts
Tuesday. In separate reports this week, two groups are calling for
an urgent changes in embassies, more authority for ambassadors, and
funds to move high-tech lagging diplomats into the modern
information age. (Malone, Cox News Service).
