companies, including IBM, Intel, Nokia, Ericsson and Toshiba, has
grown to 200. And some 350 representatives are huddled privately at
the Grand Hyatt Hotel Oct 27-29 to share information, explain and
teach the technology, so all the players can be prepared to produce
new handheld and mobile products next year. (Holsendolph, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   NAVISTAR _ SPRINGFIELD, Ohio _ About 150 striking workers at
Navistar's TSPC will vote on a new contract today that could end a
three-week strike. (Springfield News)
</P>
<P>
   REMODEL _ ATLANTA _ Americans spent $88 million on home
remodeling during the year ended September1998. During the past two
years, remodeling activity has increased 15 percent, says Harvard
University's Joint Center for Housing Studies. As further proof
that remodeling is a major factor in the housing business, it now
accounts for nearly 40 percent of residential investment. (Harte,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ Declining interest rates can be a major threat to
retirees. Often retirees depend on investment income right now _
not growth in years ahead _ to pay their living expenses. (Ezell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CLASSROOM _ Dubbed Classroom 2000, a new approach pulls together
</P>
<P>
   several media at once and brings them to bear on the teaching
process. At the same time the system frees student to fully
concentrate and participate in class without the furious, head-down
note taking that characterizes most college classrooms.
(Holsendlph, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   JONES-ASKEW _ ATLANTA _Profile of Jones &AMP; Askew, LLP, a large
Southeast law firm exclusively practicing intellectual property
law.(Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ATY2K _ ATLANTA _ Santa Claus is bringing partial Y2k fixes for
IBM-compatible PC hardware to town, and a little Atlanta company
seems to have found a better fix than such giants as Symantec and
McAfee. (Chambers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
