<P>
   FBC-GSUGSU _ ATLANTA _ Georgia Southern might have pulled off
the steal of the century two years ago when it recruited Adrian
Peterson out of Alachua High School in Florida. Peterson was a
football star with incredible talent, but a speech impediment
caused major schools to back away thinking he might be an academic
risk. So GSU assistant Tracy Ham, an Alachua graduate, convinced
Peterson to come to Georgia Southern and he has taken Division I-AA
by storm. Peterson broke GSU single-season rushing record in last
week's victory over The Citadel and has fans in Statesboro thinking
of the glory days when GSU was competing for national titles year
after year. (Reese, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATORS_ GAINESVILLE, Fla._ Florida is 5-1 and ranked No. 5
in the nation. So why are people here not as excited as normal
about the Gators? Their only loss was in overtime to No. 3
Tennessee in a game they could have easily won. Part of the problem
is an offense that doesn't score 50 points each time out and win
games as decisively as they used to. The other problem is Florida
had a very special collection of athletes in 1995 and 1996 when
they played for the national championship. They set the
expectations bar very high -- maybe too high. Despite all this,
Florida enters Saturday's game with Georgia in the hunt for the
national championship. But do they really feel like a national
championship team? (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
