<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 18:43 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9873 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TV-SURFER28-COX     10-27 0437
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-SURFER28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Two lines of headline will go in right hereg
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When baby boomers were of trick-or-treat age, they pretty much
had to make do with ``It's the Great Pumpkin, Charlie Brown'' for
Halloween specials. These days, Halloween has become TV's second
favorite holiday, and anywhere you swing a black cat, you'll hit a
Halloween show. A few highlights of the many:
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Simpsons'' 8 p.m. EST Thursday on Fox _ If you missed
``Treehouse of Terror IX'' on Sunday, Fox repeats it right away.
The traditional ``Treehouse'' anthology episode includes the first
time real people (Regis Philbin and Kathie Lee Gifford) have
appeared on the series, interacting with the animation. It's brief,
but not a bad little special effect.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Wes Craven Presents: Don't Look Down'' 9 p.m. EST Thursday
on ABC _ The filmmaker didn't direct or write this new TV-movie; he
was just one of four executive producers. It's especially aimed to
unnerve those with a fear of heights and falling. Megan Ward
(``Party of Five'') stars.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``ER'' 10 p.m. EST Thursday on NBC _ What else could young
Lucy (Kellie Martin) mess up? How about the Halloween party at her
dorm? How about next week she imitates Rosalind Shays on ``L.A.
Law?''
</P>
<P>
   -- ``It's the Great Pumpkin, Charlie Brown'' 8 p.m. EST Friday
on CBS _ You're never too old.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Millennium'' 9 p.m. EST Friday on Fox _ A horror movie is
being shot based about an old case of Frank's (Lance Henriksen).
And speaking of old cases and horror, KISS members guest star as
themselves.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Hollywood Ghost Stories'' 9 p.m. EST Friday on AMC _ A
one-hour documentary about haunted landmarks and the like in Los
Angeles. Hosted by William Shatner. Now that's scary.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Sabrina, the Teenage Witch'' 9 p.m. EST Friday on ABC _
``Laugh-in'' alumni JoAnne Worley, Ruth Buzzi, Gary Owens, Alan
Sues and Dave Madden guest-star as ``psychotic party animals.''
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Nick or Treat'' 3-9 p.m. EST Saturday on Nickeoldeon _ Nick
runs a six-hour marathon of spooky episode repeats, including
``Rugrats,'' ``The Secret World of Alex Mack,'' ``Are You Afraid of
the Dark?,'' ``The Adventures of Pete &AMP; Pete'' and ``AAAHH!!! Real
Monsters.''
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Buffy the Vampire Slayer Presents Videos ...'' 7-11p.m. EST
Saturday on MTV _ The cast of ``Buffy'' play their fave vids and
clips from the show, and take viewers on a tour of the set. Blatant
cross-promotion at its apex.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: channelsurfer(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
