</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Bob
McCarthy at the Daily News, (818) 713-3665. 
. 
HISTORY-X-FEUD (Los Angeles) _ ``American History X's'' star,
producers and studio hope that the outrageously staged complaints
of its first-time director won't distract audiences from the
anti-hate message of their explosive, in-your-face movie about
neo-Nazi skinheads. Director Tony Kaye, however, says he wants his
name removed from the film precisely because he thinks the studio
cut lionizes a racist. By Bob Strauss.  
 
  
HISTORY-REVIEW _ Review of ``American History X.'' By Bob Strauss. 
 
 
TALKIN-RADIO (Los Angeles) _ Weekly column about the L.A. radio
scene. By Fred Shuster. 
 
 
MANCINI-DAUGHTER (Los Angeles) _ Monica Mancini sings some of her
father's most famous songs tonight at UCLA's Royce Hall in a
concert being taped for a PBS special to air in December. Rob
Lowman.
<TEXT>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-27-98 1849EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19981027.0244 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-27 18:50 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9891 &Cx1f; tad-z
